    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks for the overview. i'm hearing a lot of different things from other parents though. some people are saying that these new materials are basically a way to protect kids from bullying and make sure everyone feels welcome, while others are saying it's actually really harmful and goes against what parents should be teaching at home. \n\nit feels like a lot of people are judging each other. do you think one of these viewpoints is more grounded in actual child development than the other? like, is there a consensus on what's best for kids?",
